<td>4.2 days</td>
<td>2.8 days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Client inquiry response time</td>
<td>2 hours</td>
<td>15 minutes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Top-up delay incidents</td>
<td>6/month</td>
<td>0</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Reconciliation error rate</td>
<td>18%</td>
<td>3%</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>More importantly, the account manager can finally enjoy a leisurely coffee on Monday morning instead of being overwhelmed by message bombardment.</p>
<h2>Closing Thoughts</h2>
<p>Agency account opening isn't a one-time transaction—it's a continuous service chain. From application, review, top-up to renewal, every stage has time nodes and status flows.</p>
<p>The value of a systematic kanban isn't digitizing spreadsheets—it's making information flow, surfacing anomalies automatically, and giving team collaboration a reliable foundation.</p>
<p>If you're managing more than 20 overseas ad accounts and still relying on "remembering" to drive work—perhaps it's time for a change.</p>
